  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">We revisited gluon bremsstrahlung off a heavy quark in nuclear matter within higher twist formalism. In this work, we demonstrate that, in addition to transverse momentum diffusion parameter ( <math altimg="si1.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mover accent="true"><mrow><mi>q</mi></mrow><mrow><mo stretchy="false">ˆ</mo></mrow></mover></math> ), the gluon emission spectrum for a heavy quark is quite sensitive to <math altimg="si2.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mover accent="true"><mrow><mi>e</mi></mrow><mrow><mo stretchy="false">ˆ</mo></mrow></mover></math> , which quantify the amount of light-cone drag experienced by a parton. This effect leads to an additional energy loss term for heavy-quarks. From heavy flavor suppression data in ultra-relativistic heavy-ion collisions one can now estimate the value of this sub-leading non-perturbative jet transport parameter ( <math altimg="si2.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mover accent="true"><mrow><mi>e</mi></mrow><mrow><mo stretchy="false">ˆ</mo></mrow></mover></math> ) from our results.</subfield>
